comments.body:
@edsantiago Thanks for the tip -- I was able to make it work by bumping memory up to 14GB.

In case someone else stumbles upon this thread, the issue was trying to crank up the CPU count by keeping the memory low (4 cpu and 5GB memory). I believe the rust compiler tries to use all available cores which in turn increases the amount of memory it tries to gobble up during build.

I was able to get it working fine with a single CPU core but it took 4 hrs (!!?) to get the cargo build going. Using 4 CPU cores and 14GB of RAM brought it down to 30 mins -- not ideal, but hey, that's what works for my M1 Macbook air. :)
